Shares of Boeing and Dow Inc. are trading lower Wednesday afternoon, leading the Dow Jones Industrial Average slump. Shares of Boeing BA, +0.10% and Dow Inc. DOW, +2.36% have contributed to the index's intraday decline, as the Dow DJIA, +0.52% was most recently trading 1,255 points (5.0%) lower. Boeing's shares have declined $31.27 (13.5%) while those of Dow Inc. have declined $2.71 (8.6%), combining for a roughly 230-point drag on the Dow. Pfizer PFE, -0.48%, Cisco CSCO, -0.05%, and American Express AXP, -0.57% are also contributing significantly to the decline. A $1 move in any of the benchmark's 30 components equates to a 6.78-point swing.

